##I'm gay. I'm on the front lines of the epidemic

Gayspot

Feature Introduction, Independent magazine, focus on the existence and survival of sexual minorities.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Interview, written by Wu Nan

Drop me a line at gayspot@163. Com

On the sixth day of his arrival in Wuhan, Xiaoyang was almost exposed to the new coronavirus.

Xiaoyang is from Beijing to Wuhan Chi-yuan, a medical staff. As a male nurse specializing in first aid, when he found that a patient in the ward had a rapid drop in blood oxygen concentration and was obviously suffocated by breathing, he immediately rushed to intubate the patient, it's the quickest and most effective way to snatch a patient back from the jaws of death, although it's not a skill that all emergency nurses possess.

In order to save people, Xiaoyang action is more intense, protective clothing is completely sealed in order to achieve the goal of blocking the virus. But as the motion increases, the air inside the suit is squeezed into the back, like a balloon, which explodes.

When treating a patient, time is measured in seconds. Xiaoyang is completely unable to take measures to protect themselves. And there were only two paramedics in charge of the ward, two of them working at the same time.

After the patient's condition stabilizes, because the protective clothing is very few, wears off for more than an hour at a time, plus if a medical staff leaves the ward, must have another colleague to replace, regardless of material or person, will cause the loss. Xiao Yang motioned to his colleague with tape in his back, in order to stay until the end of the day.

At this time in addition to wear protective clothing, isolation clothing, wearing masks, gloves and respiratory distress, hand ear and face pain, but also some fear in the heart.

Back at the hotel in the evening, Xiaoyang hesitated, or did not tell thousands of miles away in Beijing, is on duty at a highway junction boyfriend Raymond.

Xiaoyang cried all the way

From the year 30, Xiaoyang can not remember his fourth or fifth time to the leadership, to participate in the Hubei medical team. Just then, his emergency department received a patient back from Wuhan. According to the radiograph, the patient's lungs are white on both sides, which is very serious and requires tracheal intubation.

Endotracheal intubation poses a great threat to medical staff. During intubation, the patient's mouth, throat and windpipe are open. Although the virus can not be seen by the eye, medical staff know that a large number of viruses are coming out with the patient's severe wheezing and coughing.

At that time, the hospital's protective supplies were not enough, but people could not help, Xiaoyang and colleagues forced their heads to wear the director's accumulated 17 years ago during the SARS protective clothing. No N95 mask, just two surgical masks, no shield, just goggles. Try to intubate while protecting yourself.

Three days later, after two negative nucleic acid tests, emergency medical workers in the current alert mode lifted the quarantine. Over the next three or four days, the head of the nursing department finally changed from "not going to Wuhan to protect you" to "yes, " but still asked, "you don't have to pay, but why don't you care if you live or die? " Xiaoyang replied, "It is the responsibility of every health care worker to protect patients. ". The director burst into tears. Xiaoyang became the hospital in the second batch of the youngest medical staff.

On the 8th at 2:00 am, Xiaoyang received a text message, the afternoon assembly. Meanwhile, her boyfriend, Raymond, was still on duty for at least seven hours a day. Raymond, a detective, is now in daily duty mode because of the outbreak.

When Raymond got home from work this morning, Xiaoyang had to say, "I'm going to Wuhan. " . Raymond, quick tempered and quick tempered, knew that this was already the case. Immediately began to check the weather forecast, to estimate that coupled with the rainy days in the south of the cold and Wet, "you love allergies, have asthma... " Raymond complained, while pulling Xiaoyang to the supermarket to buy electric blanket.

March ceremony, the love to Cry Xiaoyang was separated from the dead atmosphere made more than tears. When colleagues are surrounded by relatives and loved ones, and Boyfriend Raymond stood in the back of the crowd, can only stand on Tiptoe, holding the phone to take photos, although only 10 meters away, but for gay people like a natural moat.

Before Xiaoyang boarded the bus, Raymond sent a message, "your luggage is in the bus, I have to work, first go. " Xiaoyang hurriedly turned to find Raymond, his car has arrived at the hospital gate. The second message squeezed into the phone, "I have shallow eye sockets, afraid to cry. "

It wasn't until the day after his arrival in Wuhan that Raymond learned that he had cried all the way.

To your family

At 16:37 on February 1, Xiaoyang arrived at Wuhan Tianhe Airport. The airport, which ranks 14th in the country in terms of throughput and carries nearly 40,000 passengers a day, is empty except for the Hubei medical team and ground crew. Even a few days after work, while back to the hotel before the rest of more than half an hour, Xiaoyang finally had the opportunity to climb the Yangtze River Bridge, despite his fear of heights and sweating, stood to see the extremely quiet city of Wuhan. The vast expanse of the river, at the moment in both sides of the "Wuhan refueling" "China refueling" under the neon light set off, has become calm and quiet.

Because in the emergency room every day encounter is critical or urgent patients, before Xiao Yang accustomed to busy working state. And male nurses are "physically fit" and always have to do more. After finishing his master's degree, Xiao Yang preferred to wear a nurse's cap with a cartoon pattern, which became one of his symbols.

On the night of their arrival in Wuhan on February 1, the Hubei Medical Teams in this batch were divided into groups overnight. According to the ward and time period, they were divided into four-hour shifts and duty wards. The minimum number of staff per shift in each ward is two. After Xiaoyang entered the ward, he realized that it was very necessary to configure the two people, "You can't hear a sound in the ward with a protective suit on. Plus the suit isn't breathable and you can't drink water. It's easy to faint. You need someone to pull you out. "

Because most of the medical personnel in Hubei Province are not in the Infectious Disease Specialty, until after 10 o'clock at night, the medical team learned the entire protection method and the matters needing attention systematically and practiced it again and again in the hotel, to make sure the ward is secure the next day.

It was also the last night for the Hubei Medical Team of nearly 100 people. From the next day, in addition to the more than a dozen people on the same shift who are relatively regular, medical personnel, in order to avoid contact and infection among each other, will be isolated after entering the hotel, "there is no guarantee that exposure will be completely avoided during the rescue. "

Xiaoyang is in charge of the critical care unit, and the difference between that and the light care unit starts before entering the contaminated area. Five layers of gloves. Xiaoyang gets the glove is often small, put on less than 20 minutes will strangle the hand pain, another half an hour will be numb. After putting on two masks, it was impossible to breathe, as if one were covering his mouth. Not to mention the ear, the bridge of the nose these head bearing parts of the extrusion, damage, and long-distance running ankle was worn by sealing belt.

This has already had the asthma Xiao Yang to say, increased in the sickness area fainted the probability. And even if the asthma attack, because the mask, isolation clothing, protective clothing layer upon layer, it is not immediately through the inhalation of drugs. "I can only pray that nothing will happen to me, " Xiaoyang said. "I was prepared when I applied. In all our medical staff's mobile phones, I prepared some words for my family. "

In addition, many patients in the ward, can not use mobile phones, tablets and other electronic devices, increasingly depressed mood, sometimes vent to the health care staff. In order to avoid accidents, Xiaoyang and his partner developed their two people's movements for help: The left hand to the wall, the right hand up.

The night before entering the ward, Xiaoyang forced himself to learn how to use diapers. More than $4,000 worth of diapers for the medical team were donated by a private nurse. In my previous work experience, even with long surgeries, I didn't have time to go to the bathroom. And now you want to go to the bathroom, you have to take off your clothes, you have to waste a protective device. "You can't pee in a diaper. " When you really can't hold it in the ward, it's hard to urinate smoothly. You need to find a corner, concentrate, and squeeze out bit by bit, "If it comes out all at once, the diaper won't be able to absorb it quickly. It will get on your pants. "

Every day after four hours of life and death test, back to the hotel, Xiaoyang in the southern winter and spring under the cold, hard skin bath disinfection. Raymond, his boyfriend, had bought him an electric blanket before he left, but it was no longer enough. And Raymond Chat, Xiaoyang inadvertently talked about his hotel was frozen enough, did not think of Wuhan on the Fourth Day, Xiaoyang received Raymond to buy him two "small sun. ". Lin Feng bought it in JD.com and sent it to Wuhan by SF Express, the fastest way he could think of.

"Open. " "Heart. "

Neither Raymond nor Xiaoyang noticed the date, Valentine's Day, on Feb. 14. Xiaoyang, as usual, had to work in the ward for four hours, and Raymond didn't finish work until early morning.

That day, Raymond was on duty at the highway exit. It was snowing heavily and he was a snowman. Xiaoyang said to Raymond, "wear thick clothes when the temperature drops, " and went to work in the contaminated area. When Xiaoyang came out, he finally opened his cell phone and saw Raymond's message back a long time ago: "You guard the patient, I guard you in the back. "

Xiaoyang felt bad. Respectively on the "front line" of two people in Wuhan a busy in Beijing, communication can only rely on video chat. Because the working time is not consistent, even if mutual appointment time, also because of the unexpected situation and wait for nothing. Two people in order to avoid each other worry, hard to get into a video chat, coincidentally picked a relaxed topic.

Eight years in a relationship can make two people feel less "normal" than many other lovers can easily achieve. After Xiaoyang arrived in Wuhan, Raymond called to say that all the loved ones from his work unit who worked in the hospital had gone home for the holidays. On the one hand, they were probably afraid of cross infection. On the other hand, seeing that the medical staff would be very hard, he asked them to balance their home. Raymond said, only half jokingly, that he was miserable, and that if they were straight, he would get a holiday, too. Though Raymond was joking, the ever eloquent Xiaoyang was quiet. He felt a strong sense of loss.

In the eight years they were together, he couldn't remember how many times he was woken up at one or two in the morning by the hospital to answer an urgent call, and each time Raymond got up with a yawn and sent him to the hospital. And I can't tell you how many times Raymond wasn't around, so lonely that he had to keep a pair of cats, called Kaikai and Xinxin.

The two cats became what they call a pair of "children" . In a recent chat, Raymond said that Xiaoyang was getting fat. "You're just like your son. You're starting to grow gills. " Xiaoyang smiled. "I'm fat from stress. " Her heart warmed up a little. But Xiaoyang, who cares about her figure, eats less every night when she hears Raymond say so.

To pick you up and take you home

Life in a little sweet, will let the person who has suffered bitter, feel more real. Three years ago, Xiaoyang's parents found out that their son was with Raymond, and privately approached Raymond several times. Later, his mother warned him to "stop fooling around like this, " but Raymond never told him about being interrogated by his parents. "probably worried about increasing my stress" , two people plus two cats living in each other's insistence on moving silently.

This time, Raymond had been on duty since New Year's Eve. Every day for at least seven hours, from the highway junction to the community, the streets, and even the personnel check... Those Days Xiaoyang from the hospital after work, even if sleepy, also have to wait for Raymond home, help him disinfection, washing clothes, but mouth hard, i was afraid he would come back with the virus.

Perhaps because they knew each other too well, Raymond rarely spoke to Xiaoyang about his own hardship and tiredness. When Xiaoyang signed up several times and finally got the chance to go to Wuhan to fight against the epidemic, he did not discuss with Raymond in advance. "from a private point of view, he certainly did not want me to come. " Until Xiaoyang arrived in Wuhan, the two people video chat, raymond said that in the big scheme of things, he was in favor of Xiaoyang, but when he closed the door and went back to his small home, no one wanted to push his partner into the fire pit.

Xiaoyang's father, who had been a doctor all his life, was proud of his son's actions, however, he was concerned and urged: "Do your best to protect yourself. When you enter the ward, you must check with each other whether the protective measures are in place. You must be patient and careful with the patients, and be prepared to overcome all kinds of difficulties. " And when Xiaoyang arrived in Wuhan, i check in with my parents every day.

In 2003, when SARS hit, Xiao Yang's father was in the front line of the respiratory division. There wasn't as much protection as there is now, no N95, no protective clothing. A room full of paramedics could collapse while a patient is being intubated in the emergency room.

Xiao Yang Remembers, at that time father wears 40 gauze mask and swimming goggles every time. Because the weather is too hot, there is no air conditioning in the ward, so we can only open the old sliding window on both sides to the maximum ventilation. The mask is not enough, Xiaoyang has retired grandmother bought Gauze, at home day and night sewing mask, "wake up every day to start sewing mask" , it was the only life insurance for the father is also for the medical staff in the face of illness. Old Grandma even got synovitis from it.

Today, after 17 years, xiao-yang has gone to battle with new crown pneumonia. When he told Raymond this, his parents were not yet ready to accept their relationship, but their experience at the front was a silent inspiration to the young men. Even so, nearly an hour's drive from the hotel to the hospital every day, Xiaoyang often feels ill at ease because of worry and stress.

On Feb. 25, during a video chat, Xiaoyang said apologetically to Raymond, "it's been three weeks and I don't think I can go back for a while. " Raymond jumped out of the chair and ran over to show him the CAT's heart.

In the intensive care unit, the Crisp Xiaoyang could not help but red eye socket, Lin Feng at the other end of the Lens to suppress tears, "heart, you see daddy fat again! " Xiaoyang did not tell Raymond, afternoon in the ward, because the ground slippery, i accidentally slipped and my ankle swelled up to the size of an egg.

End of video. It's almost 10:00. Enduring the pain of his feet, Xiaoyang opened the two laptops he carried with him and began to make courseware for his university courses as a tutor. At the same time, he gave a trial lecture in the form of an online course, "The class is in two weeks, and I intend to add some first aid to the actual situation. It is also an accumulation of experience and a promotion. "

And back to Beijing, estimated also have no time to repair, "now our hospital is also full load operation, estimated after going back to work immediately, now have time to get more courseware. "

Busy until the early morning, Xiaoyang before going to bed, the ear again remembered the day of his ride to Wuhan Relief plane, the captain's broadcast, "This flight from Beijing to Beijing, through Wuhan... Wait for you win, we come to take you home. "
